Euro Declines After Juncker Says Progress on Greece ‘Extremely Difficult’

-- B y   N i c h o l a s   R e y n o l d s
-- 
2011-06-17T02:51:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-17/euro-declines-after-juncker-says-progress-on-greece-extremely-difficult-.html
The euro fell against the dollar and
the yen after Luxembourg’s Jean-Claude Juncker was quoted by the
German newspaper Tagesspiegel as saying progress resolving the
Greek debt crisis is “extremely difficult.”  The single currency slid to $1.4176 as of 11:48 a.m. in
 Tokyo  from $1.4204 yesterday in  New York . It declined to 114.31
yen from 114.56 yen.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nicholas Reynolds at 
 nreynolds2@bloomberg.net  